{{Infobox Wrestling event |name=Destruction (2013) |image=Destruction (2013).jpg |caption=Promotional poster for the event, featuring [[Kazuchika Okada]] and other [[New Japan Pro-Wrestling roster|NJPW wrestlers]] |promotion=[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]] |date={{dts|2013|09|29}}<ref name=Destruction13/> |venue=[[World Memorial Hall|Kobe World Memorial Hall]]<ref name=Destruction13/> |city=[[Kobe]], [[Japan]]<ref name=Destruction13/> |attendance=8,000<ref name=Destruction13/> |lastevent=[[G1 Climax#2013|G1 Climax 23]] |nextevent=[[King of Pro-Wrestling (2013)]] |liveevent= |event=[[NJPW Destruction|Destruction]] |lastevent2=[[Destruction (2012)]] |nextevent2=[[Destruction in Kobe (2014)]] }} '''Destruction (2013)''' was a [[professional wrestling]] [[pay-per-view]] (PPV) event promoted by [[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]] (NJPW). The event took place on September 29, 2013, in [[Kobe]], [[Hyōgo Prefecture|Hyōgo]], at the [[World Memorial Hall|Kobe World Memorial Hall]]. The event featured ten matches (including one [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Dark match|dark match]]), four of which were contested for [[Championship (professional wrestling)|championships]].<ref name=Destruction13>{{cite web | url = http://www.njpw.co.jp/match/detail_result.php?e=759 | title = Destruction | accessdate=October 18, 2013 | work=[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]] | language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name=Destruction13SN>{{cite web | url = http://live.sportsnavi.yahoo.co.jp/live/fight/all/2013092901/ | title = 新日本プロレス「Destruction」 | date=September 29, 2013 | accessdate=October 18, 2013 | work=Sports Navi | publisher=[[Yahoo!]] | language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name=Destruction13WV>{{cite web | url = http://www.wrestleview.com/misc-news/44076-9-29-njpw-ippv-results-hyogo-japan-okada-kojima | title = 9/29 NJPW iPPV Results: Hyogo, Japan (Okada/Kojima) | last=Namako | first=Jason | date=September 29, 2013 | accessdate=October 18, 2013 | work=Wrestleview}}</ref> It was the seventh event under the [[NJPW Destruction|Destruction]] name.
==Storylines== Destruction featured ten [[Professional wrestling match types|professional wrestling matches]] that involved different wrestlers from pre-existing scripted feuds and [[Narrative thread|storylines]]. Wrestlers portrayed [[Heel (professional wrestling)|villains]], [[Face (professional wrestling)|heroes]], or [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Tweener|less distinguishable characters]] in the scripted events that built tension and culminated in a wrestling match or series of matches.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm |title=How Pro Wrestling Works |last=Grabianowski |first=Ed |accessdate=September 13, 2014 |work=HowStuffWorks, Inc. |publisher=[[Discovery Communications]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDla2zy5?url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm |archivedate=November 18, 2013 |df= }}</ref>
==Event== As part of the newly revived relationship between NJPW and the [[National Wrestling Alliance]] (NWA), the event featured the third time [[Rob Conway]] defended the [[NWA World Heavyweight Championship]] in a NJPW ring.<ref name=Destruction13/> The event also saw the culmination of a [[Feud (professional wrestling)|storyline rivalry]] between [[Hiroshi Tanahashi]] and [[Prince Devitt]], with Tanahashi emerging victorious in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Lumberjack match|Lumberjack Deathmatch]], which set him up as the next challenger for the [[IWGP Heavyweight Championship]].<ref name=Destruction13/> [[Tetsuya Naito]], coming off winning the [[G1 Climax#2013|2013 G1 Climax]], defeated [[Masato Tanaka]] to retain his certificate for an IWGP Heavyweight Championship match at [[Wrestle Kingdom 8 in Tokyo Dome]] and capture the [[NEVER Openweight Championship]].<ref name=Destruction13/> In the semi-main event, a rematch from [[Wrestling Dontaku 2013]], [[Shinsuke Nakamura]] successfully defended the [[IWGP Intercontinental Championship]] against [[Shelton Benjamin|Shelton X Benjamin]], avenging a loss from final day of the 2013 G1 Climax.<ref name=Destruction13/> In the main event, [[Kazuchika Okada]] successfully defended the IWGP Heavyweight Championship against [[Satoshi Kojima]], also avenging a prior loss from the final day of the 2013 G1 Climax.<ref name=Destruction13/>{{-}}
