{{Infobox officeholder | honorific_prefix = [[Director General (Philippine National Police)|Dir. Gen.]] | name = Oscar Albayalde | birth_name = Oscar David Albayalde | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1963|11|08}} | death_date = | birth_place = [[San Fernando, Pampanga]], [[Philippines]] | death_place = | placeofburial = | placeofburial_label = | image = PNP Oscar D. Albayalde.jpg | caption = | office = [[Philippine National Police Chief|Chief]] of the [[Philippine National Police]] | president = [[Rodrigo Duterte]] | term_start = April 19, 2018 | term_end = | predecessor = [[Ronald dela Rosa]] | successor = Incumbent | module = {{Infobox police officer | other_names = |child=yes |allegiance= {{flag|Philippines}} | serviceyears=1986– | department = [[Philippine National Police]] *[[National Capital Region Police Office]] *PNP Directorate for Plans *Pampanga Police Provincial Office |rank=* [[Director General (Philippine National Police)|Director]] *{{nowrap|[[File:PNP GEN Svc.svg|12px|General]] [[Director General (Philippine National Police)|Director General]]}} }} | alma_mater = [[Philippine Military Academy]] | rank = | unit = | Rank = }}
'''Oscar David Albayalde''' is a [[Filipinos|Filipino]] police officer who serves as the [[Philippine National Police Chief]] since April 19, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sunstar.com.ph/article/1507238/Manila/Local-News/Albayalde-takes-oath-as-new-PNP-chief|title=Albayalde takes oath as new PNP chief|first=Third Anne|last=Peralta-Malonzo|date=19 April 2018|website=sunstar.com.ph|accessdate=17 July 2018}}</ref> A member of the [[Philippine Military Academy]] Sinagtala Class of 1986, he is called "Odie" or "Oca" by his peers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.journal.com.ph/lifestyle/womens-journal/welcome-gen-oscar-albayalde-22nd-pnp-chief|title=Welcome Gen. Oscar Albayalde, 22nd PNP Chief|first=Alfred P.|last=Dalizon|website=journal.com.ph|accessdate=17 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709154030/http://www.journal.com.ph/lifestyle/womens-journal/welcome-gen-oscar-albayalde-22nd-pnp-chief|archive-date=9 July 2018|dead-url=no|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He is known for his command in the [[National Capital Region Police Office]],<ref name="rappler.com">{{cite web|url=https://www.rappler.com/newsbreak/iq/199631-pnp-chief-oscar-albayalde-profile|title=Who is Oscar Albayalde, the next PNP chief?|website=rappler.com|accessdate=17 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709162331/https://www.rappler.com/newsbreak/iq/199631-pnp-chief-oscar-albayalde-profile|archive-date=9 July 2018|dead-url=no|df=dmy-all}}</ref> his leadership during the preparations for the [[ASEAN Summit]], and leading the police response in the [[2017 Resorts World Manila attack]].<ref name="rappler.com"/>
==Education== {{likearesume|1=section|date=July 2018}} He is a Post Graduate a. Master of Public Administration -MLQU, Manila (1995–96), Studied in University of the Assumption, Pampanga (1980–82), Had a BS Degree – Philippine Military Academy, Baguio City (1982–86) and Cum Laude – March 22, 1986 (Philippine Military Academy). His classmates or "Mistah" includes his Predecessor and current Bureau of Corrections director Ronald Dela Rosa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dwdd.com.ph/2018/04/19/police-director-oscar-d-albayalde/|title=Police Director Oscar D Albayalde – DWDD|website=dwdd.com.ph|accessdate=17 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709155038/https://dwdd.com.ph/2018/04/19/police-director-oscar-d-albayalde/|archive-date=9 July 2018|dead-url=no|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
==Personal life== Albayalde is married to Cherrylyn Albayalde, and they have 4 children.<ref name="rappler.com"/>
